# Kale Lentil Curry

## Ingredients
- 200 g tofu
- 150 g beluga lentils
- 2 handfuls of kale
- 1 onion
- 2 cloves of garlic
- 1 piece of ginger
- 2 tbsp yellow curry paste (Cock Brand, "Gelbe Currypaste")
- 1 can coconut milk (400 ml)
- some water
- 1 splash of soy sauce
- pepper
- some curry powder

## Preparation
1. Cook the lentils until tender.
2. Strip the kale leaves from the stems.
3. SautÃ© the onion, ginger, and garlic.
4. Add curry paste and fry briefly.
5. Deglaze with water and coconut milk.
6. Add lentils and kale, let it cook.
7. Fry the tofu and add it to the curry.
8. Mix everything together. Add a splash of soy sauce.
9. Season with pepper and some curry powder.
10. Let it simmer briefly.
11. Serve with rice or naan.

